PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772234476
OL,3,CTwo dead and dozens injured after tram
OL,4,Cderails in Milan
OL,6,FThe Italian prime minister, Giorgia
OL,7,FMeloni, expressed her "deepest
OL,8,Fcondolences" over the deaths.
OL,10,FSala suggested human error was to
OL,11,Fblame, saying the driver had
OL,12,Fapparently failed to switch the tracks
OL,13,Fto keep the tram going straight.
OL,15,FThe city's mayor described the driver
OL,16,Fas a seasoned employee who had only
OL,17,Fbeen on his shift for an hour. But he
OL,18,Fsaid he had skipped a prior stop
OL,19,Fbefore the crash occurred, and would
OL,20,Fbe questioned from the hospital where
OL,21,Fhe was being treated for his injuries.
